'''Prince Kume''' ({{lang-ja|来目皇子}}, birthdate unknown – March 25, 603) was a Japanese {{ill|prince|ja|皇族}} of the {{ill|Asuka period|ja|飛鳥時代}}, also referred to as '''Kume no Ō''' (久米王). He was a son of {{ill|Emperor Yōmei|ja|用明天皇}}.

== Biography ==
[[File:Tsukaana Kofun (Habikino), haisho.jpg|thumb|220px|right|{{center|Prince Kume's burial site: {{ill|Tsukaana Kofun|ja|塚穴古墳}}<br />({{ill|Habikino, Osaka|ja|羽曳野市}})}}]]
[[File:Temporary burial place of Prince Kume.jpg|thumb|220px|right|{{center|Prince Kume's temporary burial site:<br />{{ill|Kuwasan Tōno-o Kofun|ja|桑山塔ノ尾古墳}}<br />({{ill|Hōfu, Yamaguchi|ja|防府市}})}}]]

In February 602, during the reign of {{ill|Empress Suiko|ja|推古天皇}}, Prince Kume was appointed {{ill|征新羅大将軍|ja|征新羅大将軍}} to lead a planned campaign against {{ill|Silla|ja|新羅}} after its conquest of {{ill|Mimana|ja|任那}}. Commanding an army of 25,000, he advanced to {{ill|Chikuzen Province|ja|筑紫国}} and encamped in {{ill|Shimogun|ja|志摩郡 (福岡県)}}. However, he fell ill in June and postponed the expedition. He passed away on March 25, 603, without achieving his mission. His temporary burial was conducted in {{ill|Saba|ja|佐波郡 (山口県)}}, present-day {{ill|Hōfu, Yamaguchi|ja|防府市}}, and overseen by {{ill|Hani no Inote|ja|土師猪手}}.

Prince Kume was later interred at {{ill|Hanyū no Yama Kofun|ja|埴生山}}, a {{ill|square tumulus|ja|方墳}} approximately 50 meters on each side, located in present-day {{ill|Habikino, Osaka|ja|羽曳野市}}. The site is currently managed by the {{ill|Imperial Household Agency|ja|宮内庁}}.

== Genealogy ==
The genealogy of Prince Kume and his offspring is partially documented in the {{ill|Shōtoku Taishi Heishi-den Zakkambun|ja|聖徳太子平氏伝雑勘文}} and the {{ill|Jōgūki|ja|上宮記}}.
* Father: {{ill|Emperor Yōmei|ja|用明天皇}}
* Mother: {{ill|Anahobe no Hashihito|ja|穴穂部間人皇女}}, a daughter of {{ill|Emperor Kinmei|ja|欽明天皇}}
* Siblings: {{ill|Prince Shōtoku|ja|聖徳太子}}, {{ill|Prince Shigekuri|ja|殖栗皇子}}, and {{ill|Prince Matsuda|ja|茨田皇子}}
* Wives and children:
** Wife: {{ill|Yubari no Ō|ja|由波利王}} (also known as Sakuraibari Ōjo)
*** Son: {{ill|Otoko no Ō|ja|男王}}
*** Daughter: {{ill|Hoshikawa no Hime|ja|星河女王}}
*** Son: {{ill|Saho no Ō|ja|佐富王}}
** Wife: {{ill|Hiroko no Iratsume|ja|比里古郎女}}
*** Son: {{ill|Takahashi no Ō|ja|高椅王}}
** Unknown consort:
*** Son: {{ill|Hita no Ō|ja|日田王}}, ancestor of the {{ill|Tomi clan|ja|登美氏}}

== References ==
{{Reflist|2}}

== Related Topics ==
* {{ill|Kume Temple|ja|久米寺}} – believed to have been founded by Prince Kume.
* {{ill|Kurume|ja|久留米市}} – the city's name is speculated to derive from Prince Kume.

