In February 602, during the reign of {{ill|Empress Suiko|ja|推古天皇}}, Prince Kume was appointed {{ill|Seishin Dai Shogun|ja|征新羅大将軍|lt=Seishin Dai Shogun}} to lead a planned campaign against {{ill|Silla|ja|新羅}} after its conquest of {{ill|Mimana|ja|任那}}. Commanding an army of 25,000, he advanced to {{ill|Chikuzen Province|ja|筑紫国}} and encamped in {{ill|Shimogun|ja|志摩郡 (福岡県)}}. However, he fell ill in June and postponed the expedition. He passed away on March 25, 603, without achieving his mission. His temporary burial was conducted in {{ill|Saba|ja|佐波郡 (山口県)}}, present-day {{ill|Hōfu, Yamaguchi|ja|防府市}}, and overseen by {{ill|Hani no Inote|ja|土師猪手}}.

Prince Kume was later interred at {{ill|Hanyū no Yama Kofun|ja|埴生山}}, a {{ill|square tumulus|ja|方墳}} approximately 50 meters on each side, located in present-day {{ill|Habikino, Osaka|ja|羽曳野市}}. The site is currently managed by the {{ill|Imperial Household Agency|ja|宮内庁}}.

== Genealogy ==
The genealogy of Prince Kume and his offspring is partially documented in the {{ill|Shōtoku Taishi Heishi-den Zakkambun|ja|聖徳太子平氏伝雑勘文}} and the {{ill|Jōgūki|ja|上宮記}}.
* Father: {{ill|Emperor Yōmei|ja|用明天皇}}
* Mother: {{ill|Anahobe no Hashihito|ja|穴穂部間人皇女}}, a daughter of {{ill|Emperor Kinmei|ja|欽明天皇}}
* Siblings: {{ill|Prince Shōtoku|ja|聖徳太子}}, {{ill|Prince Shigekuri|ja|殖栗皇子}}, and {{ill|Prince Matsuda|ja|茨田皇子}}
* Wives and children:
** Wife: {{ill|Yubari no Ō|ja|由波利王}} (also known as Sakuraibari Ōjo)
*** Son: {{ill|Otoko no Ō|ja|男王}}
*** Daughter: {{ill|Hoshikawa no Hime|ja|星河女王}}
*** Son: {{ill|Saho no Ō|ja|佐富王}}
** Wife: {{ill|Hiroko no Iratsume|ja|比里古郎女}}
*** Son: {{ill|Takahashi no Ō|ja|高椅王}}
** Unknown consort:
*** Son: {{ill|Hita no Ō|ja|日田王}}, ancestor of the {{ill|Tomi clan|ja|登美氏}}

