In February 602, during the reign of {{ill|Empress Suiko|ja|推古天皇|12=draft}}, Prince Kume was appointed {{ill|Seishin Dai Shogun|ja|征新羅大将軍|lt=Seishin Dai Shogun|12=draft}} to lead a planned campaign against {{ill|Silla|ja|新羅|12=draft}} after its conquest of {{ill|Mimana|ja|任那|12=draft}}. Commanding an army of 25,000, he advanced to {{ill|Chikuzen Province|ja|筑紫国|12=draft}} and encamped in {{ill|Shimogun|ja|志摩郡 (福岡県)|12=draft}}. However, he fell ill in June and postponed the expedition. He passed away on March 25, 603, without achieving his mission. His temporary burial was conducted in {{ill|Saba|ja|佐波郡 (山口県)|12=draft}}, present-day {{ill|Hōfu, Yamaguchi|ja|防府市|12=draft}}, and overseen by {{ill|Hani no Inote|ja|土師猪手|12=draft}}.

