In February 602, during the reign of {{ill|Empress Suiko|ja|推古天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Empress Suiko|qq=}}, Prince Kume was appointed {{ill|Seishin Dai Shogun|ja|征新羅大将軍|lt=Seishin Dai Shogun|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Seishin Dai Shogun|qq=}} to lead a planned campaign against {{ill|Silla|ja|新羅|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Silla|qq=}} after its conquest of {{ill|Mimana|ja|任那|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mimana|qq=}}. Commanding an army of 25,000, he advanced to {{ill|Chikuzen Province|ja|筑紫国|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chikuzen Province|qq=}} and encamped in {{ill|Shimogun|ja|志摩郡 (福岡県)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shimogun|qq=}}. However, he fell ill in June and postponed the expedition. He passed away on March 25, 603, without achieving his mission. His temporary burial was conducted in {{ill|Saba|ja|佐波郡 (山口県)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saba|qq=}}, present-day {{ill|Hōfu, Yamaguchi|ja|防府市|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hōfu, Yamaguchi|qq=}}, and overseen by {{ill|Hani no Inote|ja|土師猪手|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hani no Inote|qq=}}.

Prince Kume was later interred at {{ill|Hanyū no Yama Kofun|ja|埴生山|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hanyū no Yama Kofun|qq=}}, a {{ill|square tumulus|ja|方墳|1=Square Kofun|1=Square Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/square tumulus|13=User:Immanuelle/Square Kofun|qq=}} approximately 50 meters on each side, located in present-day {{ill|Habikino, Osaka|ja|羽曳野市|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Habikino, Osaka|qq=}}. The site is currently managed by the {{ill|Imperial Household Agency|ja|宮内庁|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imperial Household Agency|qq=}}.

