'''Prince Kume''' ({{lang-ja|来目皇子}}, birthdate unknown – March 25, 603) was a Japanese {{ill|Imperial Prince|lt=Imperial Prince|lt=Prince|ja|皇族|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/prince|qq=}} of the {{ill|Asuka period|en|Asuka period|WD=Q210688|lt=Asuka period|1=Asuka period}}, also referred to as '''Kume no Ō''' (久米王). He was a son of {{ill|Emperor Yōmei|en|Emperor Yōmei|WD=Q349281|lt=Emperor Yōmei|1=Emperor Yōmei}}.

== Biography ==
[[File:Tsukaana Kofun (Habikino), haisho.jpg|thumb|220px|right|{{center|Prince Kume's burial site: {{ill|Tsukaana Kofun  (Habikino)|lt=Tsukaana Kofun|ja|塚穴古墳 (羽曳野市)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsukaana Kofun  (Habikino)|qq=}}<br />({{ill|Habikino|en|Habikino|WD=Q694308|lt=Habikino, Osaka|1=Habikino}})}}]]
[[File:Temporary burial place of Prince Kume.jpg|thumb|220px|right|{{center|Prince Kume's temporary burial site:<br />{{ill|Kuwasan Tōno-o Kofun|ja|桑山塔ノ尾古墳|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kuwasan Tōno-o Kofun|qq=}}<br />({{ill|Hōfu|en|Hōfu|WD=Q502209|lt=Hōfu, Yamaguchi|1=Hōfu}})}}]]

In February 602, during the reign of {{ill|Empress Suiko|en|Empress Suiko|WD=Q298057|lt=Empress Suiko|1=Empress Suiko}}, Prince Kume was appointed {{ill|Seishin Dai Shogun|ja|征新羅大将軍|lt=Seishin Dai Shogun|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Seishin Dai Shogun|qq=}} to lead a planned campaign against {{ill|Silla|en|Silla|WD=Q28456|lt=Silla|1=Silla}} after its conquest of {{ill|Mimana|en|Mimana|WD=Q1790223|lt=Mimana|1=Mimana}}. Commanding an army of 25,000, he advanced to {{ill|Tsukushi Province|en|Tsukushi Province|WD=Q1206461|lt=Chikuzen Province|1=Tsukushi Province}} and encamped in {{ill|Shimogun|ja|志摩郡 (福岡県)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shimogun|1=Shima district|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11072233}}. However, he fell ill in June and postponed the expedition. He passed away on March 25, 603, without achieving his mission. His temporary burial was conducted in {{ill|Saba District, Yamaguchi|en|Saba District, Yamaguchi|WD=Q7395781|lt=Saba|1=Saba District, Yamaguchi}}, present-day {{ill|Hōfu|en|Hōfu|WD=Q502209|lt=Hōfu, Yamaguchi|1=Hōfu}}, and overseen by {{ill|Hani no Inote|ja|土師猪手|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hani no Inote|1=Q11423457|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11423457}}.

Prince Kume was later interred at {{ill|Hanyū no Yama Kofun|ja|埴生山|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hanyū no Yama Kofun|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, a {{ill|square tumulus|ja|方墳|1=Square Kofun|1=Square Kofun|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/square tumulus|13=User:Immanuelle/Square Kofun|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} approximately 50 meters on each side, located in present-day {{ill|Habikino|en|Habikino|WD=Q694308|lt=Habikino, Osaka|1=Habikino}}. The site is currently managed by the {{ill|Imperial Household Agency|en|Imperial Household Agency|WD=Q1143602|lt=Imperial Household Agency|1=Imperial Household Agency}}.

